            "description": "Fix issue 1959 balance assertion",
            "prompt": "I need you to implement a fix for GitHub issue #1959 in the ledger accounting tool. The fix is in `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-1959/src/textual_xacts.cc`.\n\n## The Problem\n\nIssue #1959: Balance assertions fail when an account has ONLY virtual postings in its history, and then a real posting makes a balance assertion.\n\nExample that should work but currently fails:\n```\n2020-04-04 Amazon.com\n  Expenses:Misc  USD 10\n  Liabilities:CC  USD -10\n  (Assets:Debts:Reimb)  USD 10   ; virtual posting\n\n2020-04-11 Amazon.com\n  Expenses:Misc  USD 20\n  Liabilities:CC  USD -20\n  (Assets:Debts:Reimb)  USD 20   ; virtual posting\n\n2020-04-15 reimb\n  Assets:Checking  USD 30\n  Assets:Debts:Reimb  USD -30 = 0   ; REAL posting with assertion - should pass!\n```\n\nAfter all three transactions, `bal Assets:Debts:Reimb` shows 0 (virtual +30 plus real -30 = 0). The assertion `= 0` should pass, but it fails because the current code (fixed for issue #543) uses `real_only=true` for real postings, which only counts the real balance (-30, not 0).\n\n## The Root Cause\n\nIn `compute_balance_diff()` in `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-1959/src/textual_xacts.cc`:\n\n```cpp\nbool real_only = !post->has_flags(POST_VIRTUAL | POST_IS_TIMELOG);\n```\n\nFor real postings, this always uses `real_only=true`, meaning the balance assertion only considers real (non-virtual) postings. This was the fix for issue #543, which allows real and virtual balances to be asserted independently.\n\n## The Fix\n\nWhen a real posting makes a balance assertion, check whether the account has ANY prior real postings in its history (`post->account->posts`). \n\n- If YES (has prior real postings): use `real_only=true` (current behavior, needed for #543)\n- If NO (only virtual prior postings): use `real_only=false` (check total real+virtual balance, restores pre-3.2.1 behavior for #1959)\n\nAlso update the in-xact subtraction loop to use `real_only` consistently: when `real_only=false`, include virtual same-xact posts in subtraction too.\n\n## The Change\n\nReplace this in `compute_balance_diff()`:\n\n```cpp\nbool real_only = !post->has_flags(POST_VIRTUAL | POST_IS_TIMELOG);\n```\n\nWith:\n\n```cpp\n// A real posting uses real_only=true so that the real and virtual balances\n// of an account can be asserted independently (#543). Exception: if the\n// account has no prior real postings at all, fall back to the combined\n// (real + virtual) total so that patterns like tracking reimbursements\n// with virtual postings and then settling with a real posting remain\n// assertable (#1959).\nbool real_only;\nif (!post->has_flags(POST_VIRTUAL | POST_IS_TIMELOG)) {\n  real_only = false;\n  for (const post_t* p : post->account->posts) {\n    if (!p->has_flags(POST_VIRTUAL | POST_IS_TIMELOG)) {\n      real_only = true;\n      break;\n    }\n  }\n} else {\n  real_only = false;\n}\n```\n\nAnd replace the in-xact subtraction loop condition:\n\n```cpp\nif (p->account == post->account && (!p->has_flags(POST_VIRTUAL | POST_IS_TIMELOG) ||\n                                    post->has_flags(POST_VIRTUAL | POST_IS_TIMELOG))) {\n```\n\nWith:\n\n```cpp\nif (p->account == post->account &&\n    (!real_only || !p->has_flags(POST_VIRTUAL | POST_IS_TIMELOG))) {\n```\n\nThis generalizes the condition: when `real_only=false`, include all same-xact posts (real and virtual); when `real_only=true`, include only real same-xact posts.\n\n## Verification\n\nThe fix should:\n1. Make the issue #1959 example pass\n2. Not break the existing 543_a.test, 543_b.test, 543_c.test, 543_d.test regression tests\n\nPlease:\n1. Read the file `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-1959/src/textual_xacts.cc` (specifically the `compute_balance_diff` function around line 390)\n2. Make the change as described above\n3. Do NOT run any build or tests - just make the code change\n",
